        "descriptions": [
          {
            "lang": "en",
            "value": "ReyeeOS 1.204.1614 contains an unencrypted CWMP communication vulnerability that allows attackers to intercept and manipulate device communication through a man-in-the-middle attack. Attackers can create a fake CWMP server to inject and execute arbitrary commands on Ruijie Reyee Cloud devices by exploiting the unprotected HTTP polling requests."
          }
